42 (9)(a) If the court permits the monitored individual a period of not longer
43 than twenty-four hours to secure another electronic monitoring service provider who
44 meets the requirements of R.S. 15:571.36, the monitored individual shall enroll with
45 the new provider and have the new monitoring device installed before the prior
46 provider’s device is removed unless the court orders another transition method
47 sufficient to ensure that no gap in supervision occurs.
48 (b) The monitored individual's previous provider shall make every
49 reasonable attempt to immediately remove its device upon confirmation that the new
50 provider’s device has been installed. Removal shall be completed within the
